How to Bermuda a Daybreak:1. Get CoPilot or Tajo 12.0, with CPBermudaDaybreak and IOBermuda.2. Get ramsysb0.loc, daybrkcp.lm, jm*.bermuda, dblisp4k.st, dblisp4k.fb3. IOP Bermuda: run jm*.bermuda as commandfile4. Stop IOP5. ResetSyms, load all daybrkcp.6. Continue IOP and stop IOP (should be at 3969 -- ENDLESSLOOP)7. Stop IOP8. CP Bermuda: BOOT CP9. Load dblisp4k (will load code and symbols)10. Set breaks at dbinitthru, PFault11. Typein: Germ12. Start CP13. Stop CP.  Place break at .CR 50014. Wait for CP to enter loop reading IOP clock15. Place 4C in TOS16. Remove break at .CR 50017. Continue CP.18. CP will stop at PFault.19. .mr+5FFF6+@(PV) contains stop of stack frame of faulter.20. @(top-of-frame+words (2,3))+5+.mv points to atom# of function